						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in a thrashing floor near the ruined Kēśavasvāmi temple in the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1243, Durmati, Āshāḍha, śu. 15, Friday, corresponding to 1321 A.D., July 10.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift made by Peddanaṅgāru of his half share in a flower-garden to the temple of Mallināthadēva, for the merit of his parents.</p>						

						</summary>
